    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Classification process or scheme that allows or exhibits linkages from one smaller context to multiple categories rather than to a single category. An example is in indexing a group of works or a complex work; as a whole, the group may be so diverse that it may be appropriately classified under multiple classification headings.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
